  "prompt": "I'm going to a wedding that my boyfriend is in, I'm a +1. I feel really nervous and anxious about meeting people in his life, is this normal?",
  "response": "Yes, this is completely normal! Many people feel anxious about meeting their partner's friends and family, especially in a social setting like a wedding. Some common reasons for feeling nervous include:\n\n1. Wanting to make a good impression\n2. Fear of being judged\n3. Uncertainty about social dynamics\n4. Worrying about fitting in\n\nSome tips to help manage your anxiety:\n- Ask your boyfriend about the people you'll meet\n- Have him introduce you and help facilitate conversations\n- Dress comfortably but appropriately\n- Remember that most people are friendly and welcoming\n- Take deep breaths and try to relax\n- Have a few conversation starters in mind\n\nIt's okay to feel nervous, and your feelings are valid. Your boyfriend likely wants you to feel comfortable and will be supportive.",
